definitions.definition: Someone from, or pertaining to Chuvashia

main_definition: Someone from, or pertaining to Chuvashia

definitions.definition: An agglutinative language of the Bolgar branch of the Turkic language family and is spoken west of the Ural mountains in central Russia . Chuvash is the native language of the Chuvash people and an official language of Chuvashia . It is spoken by about two million people.

main_definition: An agglutinative language of the Bolgar branch of the Turkic language family and is spoken west of the Ural mountains in central Russia . Chuvash is the native language of the Chuvash people and an official language of Chuvashia . It is spoken by about two million people.
